{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17603201","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17603201"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T12:34:08+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T12:34:08+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15718"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15718","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15718"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.04,0.3,0.11,0.15,0.41]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8409"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66019"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8409","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8409"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15718"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51470"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4935"},{"type":"tags","id":"4940"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4946"},{"type":"tags","id":"8501"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20254"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20256"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66019","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/66019"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe ovarian follicle contains several specialized cellular layers that support oocyte development and fertilization.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the function of the corona radiata?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Produces progesterone for endometrial maintenance","Prevents multiple sperm from fertilizing the egg","Secretes inhibin to regulate follicle stimulating hormone","Forms the basement membrane of the follicle","Provides nutrients and signalling molecules to the oocyte"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe corona radiata is the innermost layer of granulosa cells that directly surrounds the oocyte. It plays a crucial role in providing \u003Cstrong\u003Enutrients and signalling molecules\u003C/strong\u003E to support oocyte development and maturation. The corona radiata also facilitates communication between the egg and approaching sperm during fertilization.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eproduction of progesterone\u003C/strong\u003E is primarily performed by luteinized granulosa cells after ovulation. The \u003Cstrong\u003Ebasement membrane\u003C/strong\u003E is formed by the basal lamina separating the granulosa and theca cells. \u003Cstrong\u003EInhibin secretion\u003C/strong\u003E occurs from the broader population of granulosa cells throughout the follicle. \u003Cstrong\u003EPrevention of polyspermy\u003C/strong\u003E is primarily achieved by the zona pellucida through the cortical reaction, not the corona radiata.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The corona radiata is a layer of granulosa cells surrounding the oocyte that provides nutrients and facilitates sperm-egg communication.","The corona radiata is distinct from the cumulus oophorus and zona pellucida in structure and function."],"references":["Evans, T. J., \u0026 Ganjam, V. K. (2017). Reproductive anatomy and physiology. In Reproductive and Developmental Toxicology (pp. 7-37). Academic Press","Fortune JE, Yang MY, Muruvi W. The earliest stages of follicular development: follicle formation and activation. Soc Reprod Fertil Suppl. 2010;67:203-16. doi: 10.7313/upo9781907284991.018. PMID: 21755674; PMCID: PMC5316466","Zhang T, He M, Zhang J, Tong Y, Chen T, Wang C, Pan W, Xiao Z. Mechanisms of primordial follicle activation and new pregnancy opportunity for premature ovarian failure patients. Front Physiol. 2023 Feb 28;14:1113684. doi: 10.3389/fphys.2023.1113684. PMID: 36926197; PMCID: PMC10011087","Oliver R, Pillarisetty LS. Anatomy, Abdomen and Pelvis, Ovary Corpus Luteum. [Updated 2023 Jan 1]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK539704/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51470"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15718"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51470","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/51470"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-28T19:14:30+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-28T19:14:47+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8409"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66019"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCo